{
  "stem": "8842.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They, most of the time, took-- to break our spirits down, the first thing what they did is they took most of intelligentsia out of the-- of the ghetto, and we never seen them again.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They used to tell everybody that they're taking them somewhere to work.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- but they never came back.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So at this point, we never knew really what happened to them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we knew that they are-- they were killed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Knowing deeply in us, we all knew that they were killed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Parents, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They knew that this is-- this is the way they do it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so by 500 people in one time, 1,000 people another time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Every couple of weeks something was happening, and it became shorter-- smaller and smaller, the-- the-- the population.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then they told-- where we lived, they asked us to move in-- deeper into the middle of the area because not too many people were left already, so they kept on making smaller the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had to move again.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we moved again to another house, and this is when we found ourselves to live together with another family.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we shared the kitchen together.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a mother and her daughter.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I can't remember their names.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we became like sisters, and my mother and the other lady became like two sisters, and the daughter was like another sister to us.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Meanwhile, we were still together.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was a very unusual thing because they didn't touch any of us yet.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we were the four daughters, my father, my mother together-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] until that big, disastrous day, October the 28th, 1942.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Was it still in '41 or '42?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I think it was '41.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
